Hey Innis Residents! The IRC is now hiring for committee co-chairs for GAME and Environmental! This is a great opportunity to gain leadership experience throughout the school term while contributing to residence. 

To apply or learn more about the position, scan the QR code above, visit our website (innisirc.com) or find the application form through our Linktree in our Instagram bio. Please feel free to reach out to our VP Internal Nicole Jacquette at vpinternal@innisirc.com if you have any questions.

The deadline to apply is July 25th (Thursday) 11:59 pm. Interviews are happening on a rolling basis so apply ASAP if you are interested!

EXTENSION: You can now submit your design until June 19th and attempt to win a $15 gift card of your choice!

Are you a graphic design amateur? Do you want to contribute to the Innis Residence community? This is your chance to help us design our Innis Residence Council (IRC) logo for the 2024-2025 academic year! 

You can send us any ideas, outlines, designs, etc. that best represent Innis Residence and the council according to you. Feel free to play with the IRC letters and colors (brown and green) & let your creativity flow freely. Remember to include the full “Innis Residence Council” name and academic year (2024-2025) in the logo! 

Submit your design by June 19th directly to vpsocial@innisirc.com OR at the form in the QR code/bio.

NOTE: Only current and/or future INNIS RESIDENTS can participate.

Hey Innis Residents! The IRC is now hiring House Representatives! If you have applied to live in residence for the next year, this is a great opportunity to gain leadership experience throughout the school term. 

To apply or learn more about the position, scan the QR codes above, visit our website (innisirc.com) or find the application forms through our Linktree in our Instagram bio. If you have questions, feel free to reach out to our VP Internal Nicole Jacquette at vpinternal@innisirc.com.

The deadline to apply is June 4th (Tuesday) 11:59 pm, but interviews are happening on a rolling basis so fill in the form ASAP if you are interested!

Howdy Innis residents! The IRC is once again hiring!

A position on the IRC is a great opportunity to get involved with the Innis community, develop as a student leader, and advocate for yourself and other residents. You’ll also be running or assisting with a variety of events targeted towards residents.

To apply or learn more about the positions, scan the QR codes above, visit our website (innisirc.com) or find the application forms through our Linktree in our Instagram bio. If you have questions, feel free to reach out to Nicole Jacquette at vpinternal@innisirc.com or Wing Yip at vpcomm@innisirc.com (for questions specific to SMM).

Not sure if you’re living in res next year? Just don’t have enough time to apply right now? No worries! We’ll be back again in July and September with applications for any positions that are still open.

The IRC Semi-Formal took place on March 16, 2024.🥂

We would like to thank everyone who attended and made the Semi-Formal a blast! 

Hope you all had an AMAZING time 🎉
